        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 6:17PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 617 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Fresno, moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Southwestern Pearland, Sugar Land, Missouri City, Stafford, First
Colony, Fresno, Arcola, Thompsons, Sienna, Greatwood, New Territory,
Fifth Street, Riverstone, Fort Bend Houston, Fondren Gardens, and
southwestern Central Southwest.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
